@startuml ollama-daemon-state
' State diagram for the Ollama daemon lifecycle under Aïobi OS's
' RAM-budget design.
'
' Conveys: how the AI stack converges to 0 MB resident memory when
' idle, through two cooperating systemd units - the public,
' socket-activatable ollama-proxy.socket / ollama-proxy.service
' (systemd-socket-proxyd forwarding 127.0.0.1:11434 -> 127.0.0.1:11435)
' fronting the private ollama.service backend (StopWhenUnneeded=yes).
' Ollama itself does not support systemd socket activation (does not
' read LISTEN_FDS), hence the proxy indirection.
'
' Source read: scripts/15-install-ollama.sh (ollama.service install +
' loopback/keep-alive drop-in), scripts/19-tune-ram.sh (private-port
' reconfiguration, ollama-proxy.socket, ollama-proxy.service,
' StopWhenUnneeded).
'
' Canonical reference: Figure 4.8 — Ollama Two-Tier Socket-Activation
' State Machine (replaces the single-tier lifecycle previously shown
' in ai_model_lifecycle.png).

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam titleFontColor #7233CD
skinparam state {
  BorderColor #4A3C5C
  BackgroundColor #F8F8F9
  ArrowColor #7233CD
  StartColor #7233CD
  EndColor #4A3C5C
}

title Ollama daemon lifecycle — socket activation + idle unload (RAM budget)

[*] --> Inactive

state Inactive
Inactive : ollama-proxy.socket listening on 127.0.0.1:11434 only
Inactive : ollama-proxy.service - not started
Inactive : ollama.service - not started
Inactive : AI stack RAM: 0 MB

state SocketActivated
SocketActivated : systemd accepts the first TCP packet on :11434
SocketActivated : triggers the unit associated with ollama-proxy.socket

state ProxyStarting
ProxyStarting : ollama-proxy.service starting
ProxyStarting : ExecStartPre polls http://127.0.0.1:11435/api/tags
ProxyStarting : bounded 30s wait before the proxy starts forwarding

state BackendStarting
BackendStarting : ollama.service starting (Requires=ollama.service)
BackendStarting : OLLAMA_HOST=127.0.0.1:11435
BackendStarting : OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=5m

state Active
Active : model loaded, requests proxied 11434 -> 11435
Active : Ollama tracks its own last-request timestamp\nfor the OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE window

state IdleTimeout
IdleTimeout : no traffic for the idle window
IdleTimeout : proxy --exit-idle-time=300s (systemd-socket-proxyd)
IdleTimeout : backend OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=5m expires independently

state StopWhenUnneeded
StopWhenUnneeded : ollama-proxy.service exits on idle timeout
StopWhenUnneeded : ollama.service loses its last Requires= reference
StopWhenUnneeded : systemd stops ollama.service (StopWhenUnneeded=yes)

Inactive --> SocketActivated : first packet on :11434
SocketActivated --> ProxyStarting : systemd activates ollama-proxy.service
ProxyStarting --> BackendStarting : Requires=ollama.service pulls the backend in
BackendStarting --> Active : backend up\n(/api/tags responds on :11435)
Active --> Active : request / request-complete\n(timestamp refreshed each call)
Active --> IdleTimeout : 5 minutes since the last request
IdleTimeout --> StopWhenUnneeded : socket idle-timeout elapses
StopWhenUnneeded --> Inactive : backend + proxy unloaded,\nRAM back to 0 MB

note right of ProxyStarting
  Unit pair: ollama-proxy.socket / ollama-proxy.service
  ExecStart=/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-socket-proxyd
    --exit-idle-time=300 127.0.0.1:11435
  Installed/enabled by scripts/19-tune-ram.sh
end note

note right of BackendStarting
  Unit: ollama.service
  Drop-in installed by scripts/15-install-ollama.sh,
  rewritten by scripts/19-tune-ram.sh to:
    OLLAMA_HOST=127.0.0.1:11435
    OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=5m
    StopWhenUnneeded=yes
  ollama.service's own multi-user.target.wants
  autostart symlink is removed - it is only ever
  started as a dependency of the proxy.
end note

@enduml
